        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 2:30PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 230 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Forest to over Martinsville, or
extending from 18 miles southeast of Rusk to 12 miles east of
Nacogdoches, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nacogdoches, Alto, Wells, Woden, Pollok, Douglass, Melrose,
Martinsville, Forest, Morrill, Appleby, Chireno, Redland and
Central.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
